<TITLE> BGMEA seeks easy loan, LC rules </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)The BGMEA has asked the government for bank loan on easy instalment and easing of rules of the Credit Information Bureau of the central bank to help textile exporters tackle recession. The Bangladesh Garments Manufacturers and Exporters Association handed commerce minister Faruq Khan a 31-point set of recommendations at a meeting Tuesday. Emerging from the meeting, BGMEA president Abdus Salam Murshedi told reporters that the minister had assured them of cooperation. The banks should allow some relaxation of rules or special facilities beyond the existing ones, he said. The loans should be made available on easy instalments, the BGMEA chief said. The Bangladesh Bank should relax CIB regulations during the recession as loan defaulters cannot open letter of credit, Murshedi said. The apex trade body also sought 10 percent cash assistance on export price, subsidy on diesel for using generator in the garments units and waiver of tax at source and VAT on apparels. The minister told reporters a sub-committee would be formed under the task force that was constituted earlier to tackle recession. A specific package would be disclosed within a few days on their recommendations, he added. The minister asked the RMG owners to sincere in meeting the demands of the workers. bdnews2
